      • ResidentialProperty

        public ResidentialProperty(long id,
                           java.lang.String legalDescription,
                           java.lang.String address,
                           java.lang.String quadrant,
                           java.lang.String zone,
                           double askingPrice,
                           java.lang.String comments,
                           double area,
                           double bathrooms,
                           int bedrooms,
                           char garage)
                    throws InvalidLegalDescriptionException,
                           InvalidNumberOfBathroomsException
        User defined constructor to initilize class level variables with user provided values.
        Parameters:
        id - - unique value calculated or enter zero if new property.
        legalDescription - - property description of max. 20 characters.
        address - - property address of max. 80 characters.
        quadrant - - city location with valid entries NE,NW,SE,SW.
        zone - - applied zoning with valid entries R1,R2,R3,R4,I1,I2,I3,I4.
        askingPrice - - price property is listed for.
        comments - - general comments on the property.
        area - - area of property in square metres.
        bathrooms - - number of bathrooms respresented as #.0 or #.5.
        bedrooms - - number of bedrooms located in home.
        garage - - a value of 'a', 'd' or 'n' representing attached, detached or no garage.
        Throws:
        InvalidLegalDescriptionException - when legal description does not follow the pattern where [0-9999][A-Z][0-9999][-][0-99]
        InvalidNumberOfBathroomsException - when the number of bathrooms does not end in either .0 or .5 or is negative 1127V4712-24;639 Royal Crest Place;NW;R2;389591.09;Lots of space;4160.8;1.0;4;D

      • validateNumberOfBathrooms

        private void validateNumberOfBathrooms(double nob)
                                throws InvalidNumberOfBathroomsException
        A method which validates a property for the correct value for the number of bathrooms in the residence. Valid numbers for bathrooms must end in either ".0" or ".5" and not be negative.
        Parameters:
        nob - the number of bathrooms to be validated.
        Throws:
        InvalidNumberOfBathroomsException - when the number of bathrooms does not end in either .0 or .5 and is not negative
